description: The decision appears to have been influenced by "economic interests", a scrutiny panel finds.
title: Jersey border reopening 'rushed' for economic reasons
title_page: Jersey border reopening 'rushed' for economic reasons - BBC News
maintext: Chair of the panel, Deputy Rob Ward, said the report followed "concerns raised over the rapid nature of changes and possible impact for Jersey" and the panel will be "engaging as fully as possible with the views of the public."
